  "response": "Yes, Kodak cameras are still around, though the company has shifted its focus over the years. Kodak, which was once a dominant player in the film and camera industry, now produces a range of digital products, including digital cameras and other imaging technologies. They have introduced various consumer cameras, including some retro-style models that appeal to photography enthusiasts. Additionally, Kodak has a strong presence in the film photography market, continuing to produce film stock and related products for traditional film photographers. \n\nIn recent years, Kodak has also expanded into printing technologies and other imaging-related services. If you're looking for specific Kodak camera models or products, it's a good idea to check their official website or authorized retailers for the latest offerings.",
